ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course teaches you about the mechanics and thermodynamics of structures from the molecular scale all the way to the cellular scale. Much of the emphasis is placed on the cytoskeleton, and you learn a variety of concepts that can be extrapolated to related research. I would recommend this course to any and all BMEs.

This is a very chill class where you can learn a lot of interesting and new things. I would recommend the class. The work is challenging but not stressful at all, it just requires deeper thinking about the content, not just copying from notes.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I will likely use many of this skills I developed in this class to aide in my research now and in the future. We need more classes like this one.
Increased my knowledge of the subject field

This course got me thinking about my research from a different perspective. Looking at the biomechanics of the cells I study is a very interesting aspect and this course deepened my knowledge of how the cells do what they do.
